        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Septr 5615</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I had intended, my dear sir,<lb/> to request you to copy form the
                    <sic>asmonean</sic><lb/> then to the Occident, the advertisement<lb/> of my
                translation of <persName>Templo's</persName> Hebrew Grammar<lb/> when it occurred to
                me that you might<lb/> not feel indisposed to join yourself<lb/> in an attempt to
                supply good school<lb/> books much wanted. I stop, therefore<lb/> for the present my
                publication, to make<lb/> to you the following suggestion or<lb/> offer, as you may
                feel disposed to<lb/> regard it.</p>
            <p>We will jointly publish <persName>L. L D's</persName><lb/> Series of School Books to
                consist<lb/> of a Hebrew Grammar, a reading Book,<lb/> History of the Jews,
                    <add>?</add> Introduction to the<lb/> scriptures and some others; The
                facilities<lb/> you possess for publishing there I</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>must of course confess renders your<lb/> alliance a very desirable one. I on<lb/> my
                part can offer you all literary<lb/> labor required by you one half
                    <sic>expences</sic><lb/> and if you prefer it assist in preparing<lb/> for
                press, besides using my best exertions<lb/> and enlisting those of some few
                friends<lb/> I have in <placeName>England</placeName> &amp;
                    <placeName>America</placeName> for the<lb/> adoption &amp; circulation of the
                books.<lb/> Should you think well of the undertaking<lb/> may I hope to hear soon
                from you. Your<lb/> views on the subject will in any<lb/> case be acceptable. I
                think it right<lb/> to inform you at once that in <hi rend="underline">no other</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">quarter at all</hi> have I even hinted<lb/> a desire for
                combining in such an undertaking.<lb/> I think the attempt might be made<lb/> by any
                two competent persons to the<lb/> extent say of 1000 dollars each with<lb/> perfect
                safety. Subscribers before hand<lb/> can scarcely be hoped for, though it<lb/> would
                seem a “Holy Alliance” for the</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>similar purpose had been made in<lb/> other quarters.</p>
            <p>
                <add>וה' יחתום אותך בספר חיים טובים ויתן לך ברכה ושולם וכל טוב</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I only sold 2 more <sic>setts</sic><lb/> of the Prayers in consequence<lb/> of their
                coming so late—with the<lb/> Occidents I believe which we<lb/> never got till <hi
                    rend="underline">the latter end of the month</hi><lb/> I have yet had no
                receipts for you<lb/> but will hand them to <persName>Mr Joseph</persName> as
                soon<lb/> as <sic>realised</sic>.</p>
        </body>
